==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blackstrap
<hw>Black"strap`</hw> <pr>(-str⟦acr⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A mixture of spirituous liquor (usually rum) and
molasses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No <qex>blackstrap</qex> to-night; switchel, or ginger pop.</q>
<rj><qau>Judd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bad port wine; any common wine of the Mediterranean;
-- so called by sailors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blacktail</ent>⟦br⟧
